data.meta_description: Hans Johann Baptist von Straschiripka, known as Canon (1829-95) studied in the studio of Ferdinand Georg Waldm√ºller at the Academy in Vienna, and later under Carl von Rahl. He spent seven years in the army, from 1848, and after extensive travels in the East, in France and in England, he settled for a while in Karlsruhe, where he taught at the Academy from 1862 to 1869.
